# Vue: External SCSS

Always keep component styles in a separate `.scss` file instead of inline `<style>` blocks.

## Where to put SCSS

- **Components** (`components/*.vue`): one file per component in `assets/sass/`, named after the component (e.g. `ShortcutModal.vue` → `assets/sass/ShortcutModal.scss`).
- **Pages** (`pages/*.vue`): one file per page in `assets/sass/` (e.g. `pages/index.vue` → `assets/sass/Index.scss`, `pages/donations.vue` → `assets/sass/Donations.scss`).
- **App** (`app.vue`): use `assets/sass/App.scss`.

## In the Vue file

Use a single `<style>` block that only imports the external file:

```vue
<style scoped lang="scss">
@import '@/assets/sass/ComponentName.scss';
</style>
```

For global styles (e.g. app theme) use a second block without `scoped`:

```vue
<style lang="scss">
@import '@/assets/sass/app.scss';
</style>
```

## Rules

- Do not write raw SCSS/CSS inside the Vue file; put all rules in the corresponding `.scss` file.
- Use `@/assets/sass/` for import paths.
- New components get a new `.scss` in `assets/sass/` and the Vue file imports it.
